 what are character stream ?
 Character streams read text files (letters, words, sentences).
 They understand alphabets, numbers, spaces, and even emojis ğŸ˜„.
 They automatically convert bytes â†’ characters (like UTF-8 decoding).

 what are byte stream?
 Byte streams read raw data (0s and 1s).
 They donâ€™t understand letters â€” they just pass bytes as-is.

ğŸ§¾ If you can open the file in Notepad and read it â†’ use Character Stream
ğŸµ If you see gibberish or weird symbols â†’ use Byte Stream

to read a file ??
import java.io.*;

public class CharacterStreamExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        try (FileReader reader = new FileReader("message.txt")) {
            int ch;
            while ((ch = reader.read()) != -1) {
                System.out.print((char) ch);  // print characters
            }
        } catch (IOException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

// if we want better performance we can use Inputstreamreader



